                            jump to other results
                        </a></div></div><ol class="sense_single" htag="ol"><li class="sense" htag="li" fkcefr="a2" hclass="sense" id="asian_sng_1"><span class="sensetop" htag="span" hclass="sensetop"><span class="def" hclass="def" htag="span">a person from Asia, or whose family originally came from Asia</span></span><ul class="examples" hclass="examples" htag="ul"><li class="" htag="li"><span class="x">British Asians</span></li></ul> <span class="un" un="help">In <span class="labels" hclass="labels" htag="span">British English</span> <span class="eb">Asian</span> is used especially to refer to people from south Asian countries such as India, Pakistan and Bangladesh. In <span class="labels" htag="span" hclass="labels">North American English</span> it is used especially to refer to people from east or south-east Asian countries such as China, Japan, Korea or Vietnam. However, many people dislike the use of very general terms such as <span class="eb">Asian</span>, <span class="eb">Asian American</span>, <span class="eb">Native American</span> or <span class="eb">BAME</span> because they put into a single category many groups of people, who may have different nationalities, languages, cultures, religions, backgrounds, experiences, etc. These terms can be useful in official contexts, for example when collecting statistics, but if you need to refer to an individual’s background it is often better to be specific and use terms such as <span class="ei">British Pakistani</span> or <span class="ei">Korean American</span>.</span><span class="topic-g"><span class="prefix">Topics </span><a class="Ref" href="https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/topic/people-in-society?level=a2" title="Topic people-in-society"><span class="topic" href="l2:politics_and_society:people_in_society?cefr=a2"><span class="topic_name">People in society</span><span class="topic_cefr">a2</span></span></a></span><div class="collapse" htag="div" hclass="collapse"><span class="unbox" id="asian2_unbox_1" unbox="wordorigin"><span class="box_title">Word Origin</span><span class="body"><span class="p">late Middle English: from Latin <span class="ei">Asianus</span>, from Greek <span class="ei">Asianos</span>, from <span class="ei">Asia</span>.</span></span></span></div>    <div id="ring-links-box">
